## What the benchmark measures

The agent receives a natural-language question about a codebase and must answer it by iteratively querying the knowledge graph via Datalog. The benchmark scores answers as :correct (1.0), :partial (0.5), or :wrong (0.0) against ground truth. The primary metric is the mean score across all questions.

## Your goal

Propose a modification that will increase the mean benchmark score. Study which questions scored worst and target your improvement there."}
